{{Han etym}}
Oracle bone script: {{liushu|p}} – a person ({{zh-l|*大}}) with dots above and below the arms, depicting [[will o' the wisp]] around a corpse.

In the bronze script, feet ({{zh-l|*舛}}) were added to the bottom. In the small seal script, {{zh-l|*舛}} is detached from the corpse, which corrupts into the unrelated {{zh-l|*炎}}; ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' erroneously interprets it as an {{Han compound|炎|舛|ls=ic|t1=fire; flame|t2=feet|nocap=1}}. In the regular script, the top further corrupts into the unrelated {{zh-l|*米}}.
